  <h4>Drive System (Chain or Belt)</h4>
  <p>
    The drive mechanism is what connects your pedals to the wheels and transfers energy when in operation or pedaling to keep your flywheel moving.
  </p>
  <p>
    There are typically two types of drive system when it comes to exercise bikes: the chain drive system and the belt drive system. Others exist (gear dive, rope drive etc)
  </p>
  <p>
    These two are great for standard workouts but of the two the belt drive is the best. 
  </p>
  <p>
    As I stated above, you don’t have to have all of these features in your bike but you should definitely try to get most of them for a smoother and more effective workout. It all depends on your budget, and if your budget does allow it then get all of the features in your. Trust me it for the best and you definitely won’t regret it.
  </p>
  <p>
    While many biking veterans prefer a chain drive for its outdoor-bike feel, a chain drive is more likely to require more adjustments, wear down and break over time. It is also hard to maintain, you will need to lubricate your bike’s chain regularly (which can sometimes be messy). Sometimes the chain can break and will need to be replaced.
  </p>
  <p>
    The chain is higher in maintenance, but you do feel like you are riding an authentic outdoor bike which could suit your cycling experience. 
  </p>
  <p>
