  </p>
  <p>
    It is relatively maintenance free as it doesn’t require any lubrication nor do you have to replace it with a new belt.
    Because a belt drive allows for quiet operation it is much more family and roommate-friendly in close quarters or small-medium spaces.
  </p>
  <p>
    For maximum durability and efficiency, nothing beats an indoor bike with a belt drive. Since its design isn’t chain-based, belt drives lack the weakening links that inevitably wear out on a chain.
